MIAMI
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting the beautiful,
the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad
Here he depicts Miami, city of glitter and glamour, of sun and sand of gleaming highrise hotels and condominiums.
Host to millions who come for the pleasure of basking amid palms and flowers in this the hub of tropical South Florida.
One of the most renowned playgrounds in the world. Miami offers a variety of recreation. From golf and tennis to
deepsed fishing and yachting. From thorough bred racing to the
"Son et Lumière" presentations at exquisite Vizcaya.
Miami also serves as gateway to the Caribbean Cruise World. From here luxury liners offer frequent sailings in
conjunction with Pan Am's "Air-Sea" Flights.
Pan Am jets land at Miami's busy International Airport from all major cities on its US network, from Central and
South America and key European cities such as London, Paris and Frankfurt.
2001.080.235
